parameters: \n<\c[30]Dave\c[15]Trap>\c[0]\fi<Wordwrap>I made a mistake,\.\.\. giving you immortal life.

\|\.\.
Why would I presume that you'd be?
\n<\c[30]Dave\c[15]Trap>\c[0]\fi<Wordwrap>I hated the thought of losing you again..
\n<\c[30]Dave\c[15]Trap>\c[0]\fi<Wordwrap>...and being stuck here, \|all alone,\| as this... \.\.monster.
\n<\c[30]Dave\c[15]Trap>\c[0]\fi<Wordwrap>You were the only person who's ever seen me for what I am-
\n<\c[30]Dave\c[15]Trap>\c[0]\fi<Wordwrap>I'm sorry I did this to you.
\n<\c[30]Dave\c[15]Trap>\c[0]\fi<Wordwrap>In a way, \.\.this story is all about you...

\.\.
\..\..\..\.and since your life can't ever end, \|\.\.neither can the story.
\n<\c[30]Dave\c[15]Trap>\c[0]\fi<Wordwrap>I ruined the last good thing left in my life.
\n<\c[30]Dave\c[15]Trap>\c[0]\fi<Wordwrap>Jack,\.\. have you been listening to conversations that aren't your own?
\n<\c[20]\n[1]\c[0]>\fiDo you remember the third kid that you and Henry abducted?
\n<\c[20]\n[1]\c[0]>\fiA small redheaded girl, \|\.\.back at the Diner.
\n<\c[20]\n[1]\c[0]>\fiI was the nightguard you two pinned her murder on!
\n<\c[20]\n[1]\c[0]>\fiYou two have killed everyone that I've ever cared about...
\n<\c[20]\n[1]\c[0]>\fiIt's time for you to pay a bloodprice, \{\c[10]\|\|\.William.
\n<\c[27]Dr Henry Miller\c[0]>\fiWilliam was always a foolish creature.
\n<\c[27]Dr Henry Miller\c[0]>\fiAll I needed to do was make him hope.
\n<\c[27]Dr Henry Miller\c[0]>\fiHe died like he lived.
\n<\c[27]Dr Henry Miller\c[0]>\fiI didn't molly-coddle you,\|\| did I now?
\n<\c[27]Dr Henry Miller\c[0]>\fiI left you to die in that suit, \|\|\.\.50 years ago.
\n<\c[27]Dr Henry Miller\c[0]>\fiI could've saved you,\|\.\. but I chose not to.
\n<\c[27]Dr Henry Miller\c[0]>\fiYOU found your own way out of that suit.
\n<\c[27]Dr Henry Miller\c[0]>\fiYou proved your usefulness to me superbly.
\n<\c[27]Dr Henry Miller\c[0]>\fiAnd look at you now.
\n<\c[27]Dr Henry Miller\c[0]>\fiWilliam was lonely,\|\.\. deep down.
\n<\c[27]Dr Henry Miller\c[0]>\fiHe fancied himself my partner.
\n<\c[27]Dr Henry Miller\c[0]>\fiIn a way, \|he saw me as the father he never had.
\n<\c[27]Dr Henry Miller\c[0]>\fiAnd saw his time at the Diner as the childhood that was always just
\n<\c[27]Dr Henry Miller\c[0]>\fiOf course, \|I never considered him my partner.
\n<\c[27]Dr Henry Miller\c[10]>\fi\c[10]You have a vile imagination.
\n<\c[27]Dr Henry Miller\c[10]>\fi\c[10]With my voice in your head...
\n<\c[27]Dr Henry Miller\c[10]>\fi\c[10]You shall be my vessel.
